$00000007 constant FMC_SDCMR_MODE                                   \ Command mode These bits define the command issued to the SDRAM device. Note: When a command is issued, at least one Command Target Bank bit ( CTB1 or CTB2) must be set otherwise the command will be ignored. Note: If two SDRAM banks are used, the Auto-refresh and PALL command must be issued simultaneously to the two devices with CTB1 and CTB2 bits set otherwise the command will be ignored. Note: If only one SDRAM bank is used and a command is issued with its associated CTB bit set, the other CTB bit of the unused bank must be kept to 0.
$00000008 constant FMC_SDCMR_CTB2                                   \ Command Target Bank 2 This bit indicates whether the command will be issued to SDRAM Bank 2 or not.
$00000010 constant FMC_SDCMR_CTB1                                   \ Command Target Bank 1 This bit indicates whether the command will be issued to SDRAM Bank 1 or not.
$000001e0 constant FMC_SDCMR_NRFS                                   \ Number of Auto-refresh These bits define the number of consecutive Auto-refresh commands issued when MODE = 011. ....
$007ffe00 constant FMC_SDCMR_MRD                                    \ Mode Register definition This 14-bit field defines the SDRAM Mode Register content. The Mode Register is programmed using the Load Mode Register command. The MRD[13:0] bits are also used to program the extended mode register for mobile SDRAM.


